FBIS4-35644 "drnes106_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-106 Daily Report 28 May 1994 India BJP Criticizes Wisner Comments on Missile Tests BJP Criticizes Wisner Comments on Missile Tests BK2905074794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 28 May 94 BK2905074794 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] has reiterated that the country should be firm in its stand on the Prithvi missile test. The party spokesman, Mr. K.L. Sharma, said in New Delhi today that there should be no question of shelving the test. Referring to some reported remarks by the U.S. ambassador-designate to India, Mr. Frank Wisner, Mr. Sharma accused the United States of adopting double standards. He said while the American Government helped Britain in carrying out its Trident missile test, it is opposing India's Prithvi tests.
